Nexeon MedSystems, Inc. Key Developments

Nexeon MedSystems Inc. Appoints Daniel Powell as the Vice President, Sales and Marketing
Jun 28 17
On June 20, 2017, the Board of Directors of Nexeon MedSystems Inc. appointed Daniel Powell to serve as the Vice President, Sales and Marketing of the company effective as of June 26, 2017. Daniel Powell joined the company as Vice President, Sales and Marketing in June 2017. Powell has over twenty years of experience working with advanced technology products, including 12 years in neuromodulation in various leadership roles for LivaNova and Abbott. Prior to medical devices, Powell held professional consulting roles at EDS and KPMG LLP.


Nexeon MedSystems, Inc. Presents at 12th Annual Neurotech Investing and Partnering Conference, Jun-01-2017 01:30 PM
May 30 17
Nexeon MedSystems, Inc. Presents at 12th Annual Neurotech Investing and Partnering Conference, Jun-01-2017 01:30 PM. Venue: Park Central Hotel, San Francisco, California, United States. Speakers: Melanie McWade, Vice President, Emerging Therapies.


Nexeon MedSystems, Inc. Auditor Raises 'Going Concern' Doubt
Mar 29 17
Nexeon MedSystems, Inc. filed its 10-K on Mar 29, 2017 for the period ending Dec 31, 2016. In this report its auditor, Paritz & Company, P.A., gave an unqualified opinion expressing doubt that the company can continue as a going concern.


